---
const features = [
  {
    id: "faq-1",
    question: "What data cabling services does Burrowin Electrical offer?",
    answer: "Our data cabling services ensure a reliable and secure foundation for your home or business network. We can design, install, and test structured cabling systems to support your internet connectivity, phone lines, and data transfer needs."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-2",
    question: "What are the benefits of installing a modern home system?",
    answer: "Modern home systems offer a range of conveniences and security features. You can control lighting, thermostats, locks, and other devices remotely for increased comfort, energy efficiency, and security. Burrowin Electrical can assist with the electrical installation of these systems."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-3",
    question: "Can Burrowin Electrical help with the installation of internet access points?",
    answer: "Absolutely! Proper Wi-Fi coverage is crucial for a seamless internet experience. Our electricians can strategically place and install access points to ensure strong and reliable Wi-Fi signal throughout your entire home or business."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-4",
    question: "What types of CCTV camera systems does Burrowin Electrical install?",
    answer: "We offer a variety of CCTV camera system options to suit your security needs. This may include indoor/outdoor cameras, night vision cameras, and high-definition (HD) systems. Our electricians will ensure proper placement and cabling for optimal coverage and recording capabilities."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-5",
    question: "Can CCTV systems be integrated with other smart home features?",
    answer: "Yes, in many cases, CCTV systems can be integrated with other smart home features, such as smart doorbells or lighting systems. This allows for centralized monitoring and control, enhancing your home's overall security and automation."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-6",
    question: "How can I ensure my data cabling is installed correctly for optimal performance?",
    answer: "Burrowin Electrical uses high-quality materials and adheres to industry standards for data cabling installation. We test and verify all cabling to ensure it meets performance specifications and provides a reliable foundation for your network."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-7",
    question: "Do you offer any ongoing maintenance services for data cabling and CCTV systems?",
    answer: "We recommend regular maintenance to ensure the continued functionality of your data cabling and CCTV systems. Burrowin Electrical offers maintenance plans to inspect the systems, identify potential issues, and keep your network and security system running smoothly."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-8",
    question: "What happens if I need to expand my data cabling or CCTV system in the future?",
    answer: "Scalability is a consideration. In many cases, we can design data cabling systems with future expansion in mind. Our electricians can also assess your existing system and advise on potential upgrades for CCTV coverage or functionality."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-9",
    question: "Will Burrowin Electrical explain how to operate my new data and CCTV systems?",
    answer: "We provide clear instructions and guidance on operating your new data and CCTV systems. Additionally, for smart home systems, we can help you set up and configure the user interface for a seamless experience."
  },
  {
    id: "faq-10",
    question: "How can I get a quote for data and CCTV electrical installations?",
    answer: "Contact Burrowin Electrical today! We offer free consultations to discuss your needs and provide a personalized quote for data cabling, modern home system installation, or CCTV camera system installation."
  }
];



---

<section id="faq" class="my-28">
  <div class="mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 w-full lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
      <h4 id="components" class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight pt-2">FAQ's</h4>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <dl
          class="-mt-3"
          x-data="{ selected: null, toggle(value) { this.selected = this.selected === value ? null : value } }"
        >
          {
            features.map((feature, index) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-3xl px-4 transition hover:bg-slate-600/10"
                x-data={`{ id: ${index}, get isOpen() { return this.id === this.selected }, get isNextOpen() { return (this.id + 1) === this.selected } }`}
                x-bind:class="{ 'bg-slate-600/10 dark:bg-primary-400/10': isOpen }"
              >
                <dt
                  class="border-b text-lg transition"
                  x-cloak
                  x-bind:class="{ 'border-transparent': isOpen || isNextOpen, 'border-primary-900/10 dark:border-primary-300/10': !(isOpen || isNextOpen) }"
                >
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="group block w-full py-6 text-left transition focus-visible:outline-none"
                    aria-controls={feature.id}
                    x-on:click="toggle(id)"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    x-bind:aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
                  >
                    <div class="group-focus-visible:outline-primary-950 dark:group-focus-visible:outline-primary-200 flex items-center justify-between rounded-3xl group-focus-visible:outline group-focus-visible:outline-2 group-focus-visible:outline-offset-2">
                      <span class="text-lg md:text-xl font-medium">{feature.question}</span>
                      <span class="ml-6 flex h-7 items-center">
                        <svg
                          class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 h-6 w-6 rotate-0 transform transition duration-200 ease-in-out"
                          x-bind:class="{ '-rotate-180': isOpen, 'rotate-0': !isOpen }"
                          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                          fill="currentColor"
                          aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                          <path d="M11.9997 13.1714L16.9495 8.22168L18.3637 9.63589L11.9997 15.9999L5.63574 9.63589L7.04996 8.22168L11.9997 13.1714Z" />
                        </svg>
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd class="pb-6 pr-6" id={feature.id} x-show="isOpen" x-cloak x-collapse>
                  <p class="text-primary-950/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 text-base xs:text-lg">
                    {feature.answer}
                  </p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
